HEADWORD: Sweetwood
<hw>Sweet"wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The true laurel (<spn>Laurus nobilis</spn>.)</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The timber of the tree <spn>Oreodaphne
Leucoxylon</spn>, growing in Jamaica. The name is also applied to the
timber of several other related trees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

